I used to work at a lumberyard. One day a woman comes in the store with her fussy toddler, and it's making everyone else agitated. As she's coming up to the counter, the store phone rings. I pick up the receiver, the kid lets go with a horrific scream. >
The lesson of the story is, all children are emotionally fragile little dumb-dumbs
And they can be thrown into a tantrum by the stupidest things
Without missing a beat, I reply: Screaming baby lumber company, how can I help you? Laughter ensued, and I got $5 from another customer for lunch.
